sed title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b)(3), the words “placed under foreign registry, or operated under the authority of a foreign nation” are substituted for “placed under foreign registry or foreign flag” because of the definition of “foreign vessel” in chapter 1 of the revised title.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (d)(1)(B), the word “authorized” is substituted for “empowered” for consistency with subsection (b)(2)(B).","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idf709805e-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idf709805f-2930-11f1-96a8-b9bd2a0a99b5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2022—Subsec. (d)(1)(D). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/117/263"},"text":"Pub. L. 117–263","children":[],"tail":" added subpar. (D)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2008—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/181/s3525/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–181, § 3525(b)","children":[],"tail":", repealed "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/241/s303"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–241, § 303","children":[],"tail":". See 2006 Amendment note below."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (d)(2). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/181/s3525/a/6"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–181, § 3525(a)(6)","children":[],"tail":", incorporated the substance of the amendment by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/241/s303"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–241, § 303","children":[],"tail":", into this section by amending heading and text of par. (2) generally. Prior to amendment, text read as follows: “A claim of registry under paragraph (1)(A) or (C) may be verified or denied by radio, telephone, or similar oral or electronic means. The denial of such a claim is proved conclusively by certification of the Secretary of State or the Secretary’s designee.” See 2006 Amendment note below and "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/304/s18/a"},"text":"section 18(a) of Pub. L. 109–304","children":[],"tail":", set out as a Legislative Purpose and Construction note preceding "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t46/s101"},"text":"section 101 of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsec. (f). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/407"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–407","children":[],"tail":" added subsec. (f)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2006—","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/109/241/s303"},"text":"Pub. L. 109–241, § 303","children":[],"tail":", which directed the amendment of section 1903(c)(2) of the former Appendix to this title from which subsec. (d) of this section was derived, was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/110/181/s3525/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 110–181, § 3525(b)","children":[],"tail":". See 2008 Amendment note for subsec. (d)(2) and Historical and Revision notes above."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
